The Whop 3% fee vs Patreon 8% difference compounds significantly at scale — at $5K/mo MRR that's $250/mo saved ($3K/yr), which funds another tool or 10+ VA hours. The Whop affiliate system (30% recurring) also effectively turns every paying member into a salesperson, which is a mechanic Patreon doesn't have natively. Running both Whop (billing layer) + Discord (retention layer) + Skool (course layer) at different price points ($0 free / $29 community / $97 course) captures three distinct buyer types without cannibalizing each other.
